reviews.snippet:
Came across the place online where they serve A5 Wagyu and it was probably the best meal I’ve had in Japan yet. Some places bait you with the premium Wagyu tag line but it’s mostly lure in the tourists, however this place is legit premium Wagyu.

It’s located in a pretty quiet area. I think it’s better to reserve a table even though there’s no line. I was fortunate enough to get a solo seat immediately. The owner might look quite stern but he showed me how to dip the Wagyu and sauce before cooking it. When people say Wagyu melts in your mouth this place is the true definition of that. Maybe if I get a chance I’ll come back before I leave.
